UNDIAGNOSED DISEASE, RICE - PHILIPPINES: (TARLAC)
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 9 Jan 2015
Source: Balita [edited]
http://balita.ph/2015/01/09/disease-hits-ricefields-in-tarlac-town/


Farmers in Tarlac [province, central Luzon] are worried that they may not get good harvests this coming 2nd crop season due to the disease that is attacking their rice fields. So far, rice fields in [Tarlac] town's 7 barangays [council areas] are already infected by the disease.

A [rice] grower said that he noticed brown discoloration on his rice plants a week after irrigation. "The stems are turning brown from a luscious green. The sheaths or the flowering top likewise turned brown, chaffy and covered with white to light pink fungal growth," said the farmer who cultivates [rice] on 10 hectares [of] land. He said the rice plants are at their flowering stage and in less than a month will be harvested.

[Other] farmers [also have] rice fields being infected by such conditions, [and] said that [they] noticed discoloration in [their] rice fields.

Provincial agriculturist Rowena Tabamo ordered samples of the soil and the affected palay [rice]. She said that they will send the samples to a laboratory and in a week's time, will get the results. [She also] learned that the varieties used by the farmers were not approved as of yet by the Department of Agriculture [but] are still in the testing period and not being encouraged to plant in large quantity.

[Byline: Homer Teodoro]

